content.description: Climb up the finger sized crack to the blank looking face up top.
content.location: Just up from the Wave Boulder and to the immediate left of Project Perhaps?.

content.description: Just above the Wave Boulder there is an off vertical beautiful looking wall with an orange streak through it. Climb more or less straight up using small crimps etc.    Dew and I climbed half of this route. But were with out pad...someone go clean it up.
content.location: Ridge just above the Wave Boulder

content.description: Start on the left side of the Wave Boulder. Traverse high and to the right on good incuts just below the top. Hit the top jug, and do the classic mantle top out moves.

SDS on a left side pull and a right crimp. Move up to a tiny 2.5 finger edge, then move strenuously up through more small difficult holds. Finish with a classic mantle, and top out the slab. 

  This route is fairly steep for the dodge. Perhaps 10 degrees overhung?
content.location: The middle of the Wave Boulder.

content.description: SDS as for I.P. But move up and right through the iron knobs and excellent moves. Dynamic moves up high take you to a crux stab for a half-baseball pinch. Top out with a couple more moves up the right side of the face/slab.
content.location: Right side of the wave boulder.

content.description: A nice cluster of boulders and cliff band overlooking a green prarie. Three established lines thus far on The Wave Boulder. Several lines yet to be done including a tall (17ft), potentially V7? face among other routes.
